Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
set_glitch_threshold(25.10)                        set_glitch_threshold(25.10)

Name
       set_glitch_threshold

Syntax
       set_glitch_threshold

       [-help]

       [-cell <string>]

       [-failure_point {none | input | internal | last}]

       [-glitch_type {both | vl | vh | vlu | vho | vl_vh | vlu_vho}]

       [-library_pins <string>]

       [-nets <string>]

       [-pins <string>]

       [-pin_type {clock | data | latch | all}]

       [-threshold_type {failure | reporting | propagation}]

       -value <float>

       [-views <string>]

       Allows  for additional control of failure criteria for SI glitch analy-
       sis.

       Parameters

       -help  Prints out the command usage. For a detailed description of  the
              command  and  all  of  its  parameters, use the man command: man
              set_glitch_threshold.

       -cell <<string>>
              Specifies list of library cell names.

       -failure_point {none | input | internal | last}
              Specifies where the failure or reporting criteria applies.

              *

                * none: Criteria does not apply.

              *

                * input: Threshold applies when the failure point  is  at  the
                  input pin of the receiver cell.

                * internal: Threshold is applied when the failure point is in-
                  ternal  to  the cell. This occurs for multi-stage cells. The
                  failure point will be the output of the first  stage  inside
                  the cell.

                * last:  Threshold  is  applied  when the failure point is the
                  output of the cell. This occurs for single-stage cells, such
                  as, inverters.

              Default: internal and last

       -glitch_type {both | vl | vh | vlu | vho | vl_vh | vlu_vho}
              Specifies the glitch type the command applies to.

              * both: Refers to vl and vh type of glitches.

              * vl_vh: Includes VL and VH noise.

              * vlu_vho: Includes VLU and VHO noise.

              Default: both

       -library_pins <string>
              Specifies a list of library pin names.

       -nets <string>
              Specifies the list of nets the command applies to.

              Default is not net-specific.

       -pins <string>
              Specifies the list of pins or primary ports.

              Default is not pin-specific.

       -pin_type {clock |data | latch |all}
              Specifies the pin type the command applies to.

              Default: all

       -threshold_type {failure | reporting | propagation}
              Specifies whether the command options apply to failure,  report-
              ing, or propagation criteria.

              In case of VL/VH glitch analysis, it is mandatory to specify the
              -threshold_type  parameter.  This  is  because when the computed
              glitch (ROP) at any given stage exceeds  the  failure  threshold
              (when  glitch propagation is enabled), then it is not propagated
              and is flagged as failure in the noise report.

              With the -threshold_type failure setting, the  propagation  will
              stop  as  per  the  new threshold, and the failure flagging will
              change accordingly. However, with the -threshold_type  reporting
              setting,  the  propagation  threshold remains unchanged, but the
              failure reporting is updated.

              When -threshold_type propagation is used,  the  software  allows
              for  failing  nets  with  ROP  values  less than the propagation
              threshold to propagate through single stage cells.

              In case of VLU/VHO glitch analysis, it is optional  to  use  the
              -threshold_type parameter because the above flow is not applica-
              ble.

              Default: failure

       -value <float>
              Specifies  the  value  for the threshold as a ratio of the local
              VDD.

              Default: 0.1

       -views <string>
              Specifies a list of view names.

Examples
       Here are some examples.

              * The following command moves the failure point from ROP to  RIP
                for inst1/a1 and uses a RIP failure of 0.2*ReceiverVDD:

                set_glitch_threshold   -failure_point   input   -pin  inst1/a1
                -threshold_type failure -value 0.2

              * The following command sets clock failure criteria to  0.1*VDD,
                latch  failure  criteria  to  0.2*VDD  and  all  other nets to
                0.3*VDD (set before update_glitch):

                set_glitch_threshold  -threshold_type  failure  -pin_type  all
                -failure_point last -value 0.3

                set_glitch_threshold  -threshold_type  failure -pin_type clock
                -failure_point last -value 0.2

                set_glitch_threshold -threshold_type failure  -pin_type  latch
                -failure_point last -value 0.1

              * The following command sets the failure threshold at the output
                of  the 1st channel connect inside all the instances of macro1
                to be 0.2 (set before update_glitch):

                set_glitch_threshold -threshold_type  failure  -cell  {macro1}
                -failure_point internal -value 0.2

              * The  following  command  changes  the  reporting  criteria for
                latches to be 0.15*VDD (set after update_glitch):

                set_glitch_threshold -threshold_type reporting -pin_type latch
                -value 0.15

                If you need to set all the data failure criteria  to  be  0.3,
                then you need to make the following settings:

                set_glitch_threshold -failure_point internal \

                -threshold_type failure -value 0.3 \

                -pin_type data

                set_glitch_threshold -failure_point last \

                -threshold_type failure -value 0.3 \

                -pin_type data

